The paper discusses the use of input optimization methods for creating interpretable representations of neurons in NLP DNNs, which falls under the category of natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also evaluates the effectiveness of different methods, which involves machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. Additionally, the paper discusses the differences in syntax awareness between language and visual models, which could potentially involve neural networks (cs.NE) and computer vision (cs.CV) techniques.
